<item>
            <title>[FELIX-342] NullPointerException after updating a ManagedService when no Configuration exists</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-342</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Tom Remoleur reported the following issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In ConfigurationManager$ManagedServiceUpdate task : if the configuration  &lt;br/&gt;
is null (by exemple first registration of a ManagedService), at the end,  &lt;br/&gt;
you fire a configuration event but the  &lt;br/&gt;
ConfigurationManager$FireConfigurationEvent task try to accede to  &lt;br/&gt;
configuration to get the pid (line 1261) =&amp;gt; NPE&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12376564">FELIX-342</key>
            <summary>NullPointerException after updating a ManagedService when no Configuration exists</summary>
